{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a0beca60-7519-462b-971b-522c3d543423","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013wKgBXLmmHgihaNQ23mKQo","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Reviewing project files"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01URgvXx1akpjhDmGUgtCUPF","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-0c3f2597b2714121a585bba6a2ec5af1/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-0c3f2597b2714121a585bba6a2ec5af1/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"7180621c-591e-47d4-87c6-d4572d6ec3f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically around test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the current directory to understand the context better, and also think about what I know.\n\nThe key change is that starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the default test runner switched from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP). When using MSTest.Sdk/3.x, the project used VSTest as the runner by default, so `vstest.console` could discover and run tests. With MSTest.Sdk/4.x, the default runner is now Microsoft Testing Platform, which produces a native executable rather than a VSTest-compatible test assembly. As a result, `vstest.console` can no longer discover tests.\n\n\nLet me check what files are available in the working directory to see if there's any additional context about this issue.","outputTokens":362,"requestId":"A048:34F832:1C6D864:209CB39:69FEA4C4"},"id":"a36f024d-5d3c-466c-b1e8-165089a43004","timestamp":"2026-05-09T03:06:54.150Z","parentId":"d3ec60e6-2052-4e02-878d-d56db700659c"}
