{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d78c55a-8850-4d87-9e39-cd604ff1fe83","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ changed the default test runner** from VSTest to **Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP)**. Your test assembly is now built as a native MTP executable, so `vstest.console` can no longer discover it.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n**Option 1 — Switch your CI to use the MTP runner:**\n```bash\ndotnet test          # works automatically with MTP\n# or run the test executable directly:\n./TestProject\n```\n\n**Option 2 — Keep using vstest.console** by opting back into the VSTest runner. Add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>false</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nOption 1 is recommended — MTP is faster, supports parallel execution natively, and is the path forward for MSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7180621c-591e-47d4-87c6-d4572d6ec3f1","outputTokens":233,"requestId":"A048:34F832:1C6EF77:209E753:69FEA4CE"},"id":"e0b4e759-c5e2-41e3-be2c-b5b3a1b37507","timestamp":"2026-05-09T03:07:00.426Z","parentId":"72ba711c-73b2-420c-8435-d4c5fd8fc7aa"}
